org.codehaus.preon.annotation
Annotation Type BoundList

@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=FIELD)
public @interface BoundList

The annotation used to mark List fields as potential candidates to be bound to a BitBuffer.

Author:
Wilfred Springer

Optional Element Summary
 String offset
          The offset for each individual element.
 boolean ommitTypePrefix
          Indicates that the type prefix must be ignored.

type

public abstract Class<?> type
The type of object to be inserted into the List. Note that this allows you to have a field of a super type of the actual type that you expect to inject. So you might have something like this: 

         class A {
         }
 

         class B extends A {
         }
 

         ...
         @BoundList(type="B")
         private List<A>; // List will contain instances of B.
         ...

Returns:
The type of object to be inserted.
Default:
java.lang.Void.class

types

public abstract Class<?>[] types
The types of objects to be decoded. Use this if you want the framework to select a certain class based on a couple of leading bits prefixing the actual data. Note that it expects every type in the array to have the TypePrefix annotation.

Returns:
The types of object to be decoded.
Default:
{}

size

public abstract String size
The size of the List. Is expected to be interpreted as a Limbo expression.

Returns:
The size of the List, as a Limbo expression.
Default:
""

offset

public abstract String offset
The offset for each individual element. A Limbo expression, accepting a parameter 'index', representing the current index. So an expression could be index*2 or offsets[index], assuming that a certain offsets variable would be in scope.

Returns:
A Limbo expression, representing the offset for the individual elements.
Default:
""

ommitTypePrefix

public abstract boolean ommitTypePrefix
Indicates that the type prefix must be ignored. Note that this is fairly experimental. Use this with cause.

Default:
false

selectFrom

public abstract Choices selectFrom
The choices to select from, based on a prefix of a certain size.

Returns:
The choices to select from, based on a prefix of a certain size.
Default:
@org.codehaus.preon.annotation.Choices(alternatives={})
